Description: Sherd from wall of large pottery open vessel; glaze fired dull orange-brown; pinkish clay with white inclusions; inside glazed; exterior: silhouette style fight: leg of one male to left; fallen man attacked by striding male; below, very broad band between lines; reserved at bottom of sherd.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.727)
